  "chunk_index": 37,
  "summary": "Colin Lamb visits apartment number 77 to return a silver-white fruit knife that he found after it was dropped from a window. He is met by Ingrid, a tall, blonde Norwegian woman with limited English proficiency who is currently cooking. Ingrid leads Lamb to the living room, where he meets Geraldine Mary Alexandrina Brown, a highly intelligent nine or ten-year-old girl with a plaster cast on her leg.\n\nDuring their conversation, Geraldine shares personal details, noting that her mother died in a plane crash when she was an infant and that her father works at the Cattin's Mill Filament Factory in Harebridge. She explains that Ingrid has lived with them for two weeks and is teaching her Norwegian. Geraldine describes her habit of using a high-quality telescope to observe the neighborhood and record details about the residents in a notebook, often assigning them nicknames, such as \"the Countess Kalarabas\" for a woman living in a house with messy trees.\n\nGeraldine mentions that her leg injury was caused by nearly being run over by a bus and notes that the house next door is occupied by a blind woman. The conversation turns to the local murder case when Geraldine reveals that the caretaker, Harry, told her about it. Geraldine claims she witnessed the aftermath of the event, stating she heard a scream and saw someone running out of the house, which signaled that something had occurred.",
